						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in the temple of Gangamma.</p>						

						<p>[Dēvarāya II], A.D. 1432.</p>						

						<p>Dated Śaka 135[4], <hi rend="italic">Parīdhāvin, Kārttika,</hi> śu. 11, Thursday, corresponding to A.D. 1432, November 3. The weekday however was Monday.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record the gift of certain incomes from the festivals (details lost), made to the goddess by • • • rāmayya (NDI, Part I, p. 313, D 20).</p>						

						</summary>
